Detailed Description

The section has a list of all the error codes which are generated by the CRC Driver module.

Macro Definition Documentation

#define ADCBuf_STATUS_ERROR   (MMWAVE_ERRNO_ADCBUF_BASE - 1)

Generic error status code returned by ADCBuf_control().

ADCBuf_control() returns ADCBuf_STATUS_ERROR if the control code was not executed successfully.

#define ADCBuf_STATUS_INVALID_CMD   (MMWAVE_ERRNO_ADCBUF_BASE - 5)

An error status code returned by ADCBuf_control() for invalid command codes.

ADCBuf_control() returns ADCBuf_STATUS_INVALID_CMD if the control code is not recognized by the driver implementation.

#define ADCBuf_STATUS_INVALID_PARAMS   (MMWAVE_ERRNO_ADCBUF_BASE - 4)

An error status code returned by ADCBuf_control() for invalid input parameters.

ADCBuf_control() returns ADCBuf_STATUS_INVALID_PARAMS if the control code gets invalid parameters.

#define ADCBuf_STATUS_NOT_IMPLEMENTED   (MMWAVE_ERRNO_ADCBUF_BASE - 3)

An error status code returned by ADCBuf_control() for feature not implemented.

ADCBuf_control() returns ADCBuf_STATUS_NOT_IMPLEMENTED if the control command was not supported.

#define ADCBuf_STATUS_UNDEFINEDCMD   (MMWAVE_ERRNO_ADCBUF_BASE - 2)

An error status code returned by ADCBuf_control() for undefined command codes.

ADCBuf_control() returns ADCBuf_STATUS_UNDEFINEDCMD if the control code is not recognized by the driver implementation.
